1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,728
Open source voice AI just hit a major milestone.

2
00:00:03,828 --> 00:00:11,810
Three groundbreaking tools have been released this month that together make the entire voice AI stack completely open source.

3
00:00:11,910 --> 00:00:14,363
Let's dive into what this means.

4
00:00:14,463 --> 00:00:21,169
First up is Jeopard 1.0, a 600 million parameter streaming text-to-speech model released under Apache 2.0.

5
00:00:21,269 --> 00:00:25,848
What makes Jeopard special is that it speaks as text arrives.

6
00:00:25,948 --> 00:00:28,826
No more waiting for the full sentence.

7
00:00:28,926 --> 00:00:32,654
It's built for real-time dialogue with incredibly low latency.

8
00:00:32,754 --> 00:00:39,885
This makes it perfect for voice assistants, live captioning, and interactive applications where natural conversation flow matters.

9
00:00:39,985 --> 00:00:42,863
And it's completely free and open source.

10
00:00:42,963 --> 00:00:50,095
The team behind Voice Arena launched VoiceArena.com, a public leaderboard that compares speech-to-text and text-to-speech models head-to-head.

11
00:00:50,195 --> 00:00:56,475
This is huge for developers trying to pick the right model for their use case.

12
00:00:56,575 --> 00:01:02,431
You can see word error rates, latency, and naturalness scores across dozens of models.

13
00:01:02,531 --> 00:01:06,685
It brings transparency and competition to the voice AI space.

14
00:01:06,785 --> 00:01:15,192
Longcat Avatar is an open source tool that turns a single photo and an audio file into a talking video.

15
00:01:15,292 --> 00:01:20,297
It generates realistic lip sync and head movements. The implications are massive.

16
00:01:20,397 --> 00:01:27,954
Content creators, educators, and businesses can now generate talking head videos without expensive studio equipment or proprietary software.

17
00:01:28,054 --> 00:01:34,334
Jeopard for voice generation, Voice Arena for model comparison, and Longcat Avatar for video creation.

18
00:01:34,434 --> 00:01:41,141
The full voice AI stack is now open, accessible, and ready for you to build with.

19
00:01:41,241 --> 00:01:43,268
The tipping point is here.

